speech.p:
asked the Postmaster-General (1) if, in the light of his announcement of a Household


Delivery Service, he will re-examine the postal delivery arrangements in the Greater London area, particularly with regard to the time of the first and main delivery;

(2) what was the average time of the first postal delivery on ordinary days in the Greater London area prior to September, 1939; and what is the average time of the first delivery in the same area in 1964.
